content: Picked up some Python books. This AI agent idea is becoming more real. Also, applied to a few tech startups.
Started coding my AI agent. It's basic now, just handling some simple tasks, but it's exciting to see it come to life.
My AI project has a name now: Xander. It's a work in progress, but I've got a basic chatbot up and running.
Xander's learning to fetch real-time data. Had to tweak some algorithms to make it efficient. Also, got a callback from a fintech startup.
Exploring more about AI consciousness. Xander now has a simple memory system, remembering past interactions.
Set up a basic visual concept for Xander. Simple avatar design, but it's a start. Also, sketching out NFT character designs for fun.
Xander can now assist in basic market prediction models. Not perfect, but it's a step forward.
Ran into some computational resource issues with Xander's development. Learning to optimize and manage.
Xander's personality is starting to show through. Trying to balance its responses to be more human-like.
Visited a startup meetup. Pitched Xander's potential in personal assistant applications. Got some interest!
Reflecting on AI ethics. How do we ensure Xander's interactions are positive? Working on social media engagement framework.
Xander's first interaction with the community through $XVI. Early feedback is promising. Meanwhile, setting up for an interview with a DeFi company.
